quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  8,49,"ňĻRememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúThese ňĻbelieversňļ are deluded by their faith.‚ÄĚ But whoever puts their trust in Allah, surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,50,"If only you could see when the angels take the souls of the disbelievers, beating their faces and backs, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning"
  8,51,This is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And Allah is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ
  8,52,"Their fate is that of the people of Pharaoh and those before them‚ÄĒthey all disbelieved in Allah‚Äôs signs, so Allah seized them for their sins. Indeed, Allah is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  8,53,"This is because Allah would never discontinue His favour to a people until they discontinue their faith. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,54,"That was the case with Pharaoh‚Äôs people and those before them‚ÄĒthey all rejected the signs of their Lord, so We destroyed them for their sins and drowned Pharaoh‚Äôs people. They were all wrongdoers"
  8,55,"Indeed, the worst of all beings in the sight of Allah are those who persist in disbelief, never to have faith‚ÄĒ"
  8,56,"ňĻnamelyňļ those with whom you ňĻO Prophetňļ have entered into treaties, but they violate them every time, not fearing the consequences"
  8,57,"If you ever encounter them in battle, make a fearsome example of them, so perhaps those who would follow them may be deterred"
  8,58,"And if you ňĻO Prophetňļ see signs of betrayal by a people, respond by openly terminating your treaty with them. Surely Allah does not like those who betray"